From: Cline (audit B2) <audit@ask>
Date: Tue, 05 May 2026 10:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fci: gate NETLINK_FF inbound on CAP_NET_ADMIN

Audit finding fci F-02 (plans/audit/AUDIT-fci.md).

__fci_fe_inbound_data() is the kernel-side handler for every message
sent to the NETLINK_FF socket created by netlink_kernel_create() at
fci.c:123. The handler dispatches into fci_fe_inbound_parser() which
programs FCI flow rules (5-tuple offload, conntrack hooks, IPsec SA
entries) into cdx — i.e., reconfigures the fast-path data plane.

NETLINK_FF is a custom protocol number with no NETLINK_DGRAM
permissions wiring. There is no nla_policy on the inbound payload
(audit fci F-01 covers payload validation, this patch covers the
authorization gate). Any process with CAP_NET_RAW (or the systemd
default of CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE) can socket(AF_NETLINK,
SOCK_RAW, NETLINK_FF) and feed the handler.

netlink_capable() is the canonical netlink authorization helper —
it consults the credentials of the SENDER of the message (not the
current task), which matters because __fci_fe_inbound_data runs in
softirq context after netlink_unicast deferred the dispatch.

Per Documentation/networking/netlink-spec.rst the correct deny
behaviour for an unauthorized inbound is to drop silently and bump
an error counter (matches the existing rx_msg_err pattern at
fci.c:485, 508). Returning an error to userspace is not possible
from a netlink_kernel_create input handler — the function is void.

Audit reference: plans/audit/AUDIT-fci.md F-02
Signed-off-by: Cline <audit@ask>
---
diff --git a/fci/fci.c b/fci/fci.c
--- a/fci/fci.c
+++ b/fci/fci.c
@@ -456,6 +456,21 @@ static void __fci_fe_inbound_data(struct sk_buff *skb)
 struct sk_buff *nskb;
 FCI_MSG *fci_msg, *fci_rep;
 int rc;
+
+/* B2/F-02: NETLINK_FF has no per-protocol capability wiring; the
+ * inbound handler is reachable from any task that can
+ * socket(AF_NETLINK, SOCK_RAW, NETLINK_FF). Every command
+ * dispatched from here reconfigures the fast-path data plane
+ * (5-tuple offload, conntrack hooks, IPsec SA entries) via cdx.
+ * Drop unauthorized senders silently and bump rx_msg_err to
+ * preserve the existing telemetry pattern. netlink_capable()
+ * checks the sender's creds (not current task), which is the
+ * correct semantic in the deferred softirq dispatch path. */
+if (!netlink_capable(skb, CAP_NET_ADMIN))
+{
+this_fci->stats.rx_msg_err++;
+return;
+}
 
 FCI_PRINTK(FCI_INBOUND, "FCI: %s\n", __func__);